subSubSection.paragraph:
Structure. Body outline subrectangular. Antennae 7-segmented with one rhinarium on each of segments 3 and 5, and two on segment 7 (
Fig. 162
). Head and wing buds with a few lanceolate setae dorsally. Thoracic tergites small. Forewing buds moderately large, without humeral lobes. Margins of wing buds bearing 10‒12 subacute or truncate lanceolate setae. Legs relatively long and slender with fused tibiotarsus, claws absent; apex of tarsus slender, curved; tarsal arolium small, fan-shaped. Caudal plate (
Fig. 173
) truncate apically, bearing marginal lanceolate setae slightly larger than those of wing buds; dorsum covered in scale-like microsculpture with each a submedian and sublateral longitudinal row of large lanceolate setae on either side and a median longitudinal row of very small lanceolate setae. Anus terminal; circumanal ring consisting of one row of elongate pores; very small; additional pore fields present on either side of circumanal ring.
